						               													<description>&amp;quot;You have earned a fortune, and you want to give it away to charity, but you can't help acquiring more money. don't give it all away though, or you are back where you started!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game components: box, board, 1 die, 8 playing pieces, 50 charity  cards, 50 income cards, 88 silly cards, 100 quiz cards, play-money&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Simple roll-and-move race game on a 64-space track, which includes a loop in the middle. Players start with $10,000,000 and have to give as much away as possible. The player with the *least* amount of money when one player reaches the finish space wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The main types of spaces are:&amp;#10;- Charity space: draw a 'charity' card and give away (to the  bank) the amount of money indicated.&amp;#10;- Income space; draw an 'income' card and collect the amount indicated from the bank.&amp;#10;- Quiz space: answer the charity-related trivia question on a 'quiz' card correctly and move to the next charity space, answer incorrectly and move to the next income space. &amp;#10;- Silly space: follow the instructions on a 'silly' card correctly (or not) to gain a bonus/penalty.&amp;#10;Other spaces include Black Hole, Insurance, Miss a turn, Throw again, Move forward, and Go back.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game was endorsed by 10 high-profile Australian charities, whose logos feature on the board and box: MS Australia, National Stroke Foundation, Asthma Foundation, Make-a-Wish Foundation, Royal Blind Society, Victor Chang Cardiac Research Institute, Lifeline, Legacy, Barnardos Australia, and the RSPCA.&amp;#10;$7.50 from each game sold was given to these charities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
